Errors handler uses app config for enabling and disabling exceptions. Recommended to use false for production.
Optionally can be used config 'errors' for custom error messages. If any message given it will be used, unless
it is 'message'. In that case it will be used exceptions message to be displayed to the users.

Example:

$cnf[400] = 'message';
$cnf[401] = 'Unauthorized!';
$cnf[404] = 'Not Found!';